MVC 
M - Model
	- Pojo/DT(Data Transfer)/VO(Value Object)/BO(Bussiness Object)
V - View
	- UI/Presentation layer
	- for web application the UI is a web page(html & JSP)
C - Controller
	- manager/brain
	- we use a servlet as controller


implicit objects of jsp
-----------------------
out
request
response
session
application
and more..

jsp tags category
-------------------
1) scriplet tags - <%   %>
	- whenever we want to write java code in jsp file, write within a scriplet tag
2) directive tags - <%@   %>
	- these tags give global information about the page
	- 3 types
		a) page directive
			- <%@page import="java.time.LocalDateTime"%>
		b) include directive
			- we can include another page in to the current jsp page
		c) taglib directive
			- used for custom jsp tags

3) expression tags - <%=  %>
	- this is a shortcut for <% out.println(); %>
4) declaration tags - <%!   %>
	- here we can declare variables and define methods in side declaration tag
	- these are placed outside the service method(in other words class level) when converted to servlets
5) action tags - <jsp:action   ></jsp:action>
	- some of the jsp action tags are
		- jsp:include
		- jsp:forward
		- jsp:setProperty
		- jsp:getProperty
		- jsp:param